ss experience, but is itself engaging critically with the question of empathy and its limits.Key FeaturesProvides a strong conceptual underpinning for the notion of empathy, drawing on phenomenology and feminist affect theoryRelates the idea of empathy not only to the clinical relation but also to medicine more broadly definedRepositions literature’s role in the medical humanities from a vehicle to access patient experience to a strategic intervention into current debates on empathy and its effects  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEmpathy in literature. 0aEnglish fictiony21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish literaturey21st centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aEnglish literaturezGreat BritainxHistory and criticism. 0aMedicine in literature. 0aPsychology in literature. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831107814030 cprintz978074868618640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780748686193?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748686193423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748686193/original  a978-3-11-078140-3  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK